22/07/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The new government of Prime Minister-designate Boyko Borisov will be officially sworn in on July 27th after receiving a vote of confidence in parliament, Parliament Speaker Tsetska Tsacheva announced on Tuesday. 
In order to assume power, the new government needs a simple majority of votes in parliament. 
As all right-centrist parties have pledged to vote in support of the new Citizens for the European Development of Bulgaria (GERB) cabinet, approval is expected to go smoothly. 
(Darik, Sofia news agency, BGNES, Mediapool, Focus - 21/07/09)
